                <h1>Responsive CSS Background Images Made Easy</h1>
                <p>To make CSS background images responsive, use the `background-size` property set to `cover` or `contain`. This allows the image to adapt to varying screen sizes while maintaining its aspect ratio. Use media queries for further adjustments, ensuring a seamless experience across devices. Remember to optimize images for faster loading.</p>
